Whitesand Memo

Whitesand image can be run on both PB and WS board.
WS supports both Annex C (6 MHz) and Annex A (8 MHz).
Default mode is annex A.

To change mode, (config)# video 4 annex {a|c}
The line card will be reset.

The ASI output should be acceptable for normal professional decoder.
Special STB however are needed to accept the RF channel, even in Annex C
mode since the FEC is different.


WS current has a bug which disable QNX image download from Rommon.
To work around, add this to the configuration:
    video 4 switch vlan 202 debug
    int g4/16
    switchport access vlan 202

This will make g4/16 visible, and add it explicitly on vlan 202

In annex A mode, 2 GE ports will be used for input.
In annex C mode, only 1 GE port will be used.


----------------------------------------
To allow WS tftp download:

video 4 switch vlan 202 debug
int g4/16
switchport access vlan 202
do show vlan

